A vintage 1970s children's television set with rabbit ear antennas sits in a dimly lit living room, its screen glowing with an eerie green tint displaying a fuzzy broadcast of alien puppet creatures with ridged foreheads and fierce expressions gathered on a colorful street corner. The wallpaper behind features faded orange and brown geometric patterns typical of the era. A half-eaten bowl of cereal sits abandoned on shag carpet in the foreground, milk slightly curdled. The TV casts long shadows across the room, creating an unsettling juxtaposition between innocent childhood nostalgia and something distinctly otherworldly. Warm tungsten lighting mixed with the cold cathode ray glow. Kodachrome film grain texture throughout.
